        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-10 11:47:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSorry for not being clearer.\nI think that in this case, Sonar got it wrong.  I believe the lambda function here makes the code less readable and thus less maintainable. Unfortunately, LF doesn't allow us to suppress Sonar findings or customize the rules to match project standards - which is another reason that going forward its best not to focus on Sonar issues.",
